$interpreted: Edward: Jo-Jo? I thought you left? Why did you come back?
Joan: Don't you like me? Why didn't you follow me?
Edward: I...I cannot fall for you...
Edward: Jo-Jo, it's best that you forget about me...
Joan: Eh? Why can't you fall for me?
Edward: There's a family heirloom, a necklace, that was stolen by the wicked nobles.
Edward: That necklace, it must be given to one's bride on the day of her wedding. It has been handed down from my grandmother to my mother.
Joan: Wicked noble? Who was it?
Edward: Ace Aldric.
Joan: Aldric? A noble from the Kingdom of the Sun?
Edward: Yes. Ace is now the master of the Aldric household. There's no way I can oppose him...
Joan: No!!! What a dirty, rotten, piece of ——
Edward: —If I don't get that necklace, then I cannot marry. Therefore, we cannot be together...
Edward: My little Jo-Jo, it's best that you forget that we ever met...
Joan: Unacceptable! Who dares stop a young woman from falling in love!
Joan: 1st rule of being a thief: No matter where you are, don't forget to make a grand entrance!
Joan: Don't be fooled by my stunning looks...behold!
Joan: The Thief of the Gleaming Star is here!
Joan: Forgive me, I must ask you to quiet down...just for tonight.
Joan: 3rd rule of being a thief: Steal back what is rightfully yours.
Joan: In this world, there's nothing I can't steal, only things I don't want to steal!
